      "en": {
        "name": "Ventilation mode - Other/advanced",
        "category": "Ventilation",
        "subcategory": "Ventilation mode",
        "shortDescription": "Other/advanced ventilation modes — APRV, CMV family, high-frequency (HFOV/HFJV/HFPPV) and NAVA.",
        "longDescription": "## Definition & Clinical Context\n\nVentilation modes that do not fall under the pressure-controlled, volume-controlled, or spontaneous/support categories — airway pressure release ventilation (APRV), the continuous mandatory ventilation (CMV) family, high-frequency modes (oscillatory HFOV, jet HFJV, positive-pressure HFPPV), neurally adjusted ventilatory assist (NAVA), and continuous-flow apnoeic ventilation. In source data this is a **procedure** record indicating the ventilation mode in use; there is no unit. It is recorded in intensive care and anaesthesia for ventilated patients. The mode is independent of whether ventilation is invasive or non-invasive — that distinction is captured in the Invasive mechanical ventilation and Non-invasive ventilation concept sets.\n\n## Included Concepts\n\nThe set lists the SNOMED procedure concepts for these modes.\n\n- *1243692 / 1297240007 — Neurally adjusted ventilatory assist (SNOMED)*\n- *4055376 / 243153009 — High frequency positive pressure ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *4055377 / 243154003 — High frequency jet ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *4072515 / 243143008 — Airway pressure release ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *4074666 / 243155002 — High frequency oscillatory ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *37151336 / 1187022003 — Continuous mandatory ventilation volume-control inflation-type and assured constant airway pressure adjunct in the expiratory phase (SNOMED)*\n- *37151337 / 1187023008 — Continuous mandatory ventilation pressure-control inflation-type (SNOMED)*\n- *37151338 / 1187024002 — Continuous mandatory ventilation pressure-control inflation-type and assured constant airway pressure adjunct (SNOMED)*\n- *37151339 / 1187025001 — Continuous mandatory ventilation volume-targeted pressure-control inflation-type (SNOMED)*\n- *37152407 / 1186742007 — Intermittent mandatory ventilation with synchronized-termination pressure-control and assured constant airway pressure adjunct (SNOMED)*\n- *37152413 / 1186749003 — Continuous mandatory ventilation volume-control inflation-type (SNOMED)*\n- *37153603 / 1222606000 — Continuous mandatory ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *37153604 / 1222607009 — Continuous mandatory ventilation with sigh (SNOMED)*\n- *37157167 / 1197612007 — Intermittent mandatory ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *37157430 / 1217390002 — Intermittent mandatory ventilation with synchronized-termination pressure control and assured constant airway pressure adjunct during the inflation phase (SNOMED)*\n- *37158487 / 1260411001 — Continuous flow apneic ventilation (SNOMED)*\n\n## Mapping Notes\n\n- Map a recorded ventilation mode to the matching concept here when it does not fit the pressure-controlled (PCV), volume-controlled (VCV) or spontaneous/support mode sets.\n- **High-frequency** modes (HFOV, HFJV, HFPPV) and **NAVA** are grouped here as advanced/atypical modes rather than in their own sets.\n- **Mode vs ventilation act**: this set captures the *mode* only; whether the patient is on invasive or non-invasive ventilation is recorded separately (Invasive mechanical ventilation / Non-invasive ventilation concept sets).\n"
      },
